        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "It's unclear how to design this to (completely) avoid the danger of false positives. A warning that you cannot resolve is harmful, and the \"record of truth\" is inaccessible since there does not exist a list of filetypes (and cannot, since these may be dynamic, see the linked `vim.filetype` issue).\n\nMaybe hardcode a list of \"known footguns\" (common languages where the Vim filetype is not the \"obvious\" one you would expect from VS Code etc.)? Generally, I think the confusion between (Vim) \"filetypes\" and \"language names\" and \"extensions\" is a much more general problem and will bite new users sooner or later. (E.g., treesitter has a similar problem with \"language/parser name\" != \"filetype\"...)",
