        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Ahreed there, and I think a static list is a good compromise for common filetypes to avoid the 99% case.\n\nHowever, what are your thoughts on supplementing this solution with another improvement to the heuristic of ft detection:\n\nIncluding the non-dynamic, user-specified filetypes.\n\nI propose this because\n\n1. it doesn't make the ft recogniztion *more wrong*\n2. Will resolve manyif not most (generalization here, but come on) filetype issues related to this issue \n3. Most (another generalization) people do not use dynamic filetypes; and this is such a quirky thing that I agree first-class support and recognition of these doesn't make sense (not to mention the complexity of invoking some random user-specified function)\n4. It is simple implementation (I think)",
