        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> Including the non-dynamic, user-specified filetypes.\n\nAbsolutely opposed. A significant number of built-in filetypes are dynamic in this way (i.e., the return value of a function checking file contents or environment variables), so this will be a very patchy list that may even miss relevant filetypes for _this_ purpose. And even if not, we're talking about a general API that people may use (then incorrectly) for other purposes, and that is very dangerous. (How would you even document this? \"Returns a partial list of filetypes known to Vim. May or may not contain the one you need.\")",
