        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> the \"record of truth\" is inaccessible since there does not exist a list of filetypes (and cannot, since these may be dynamic, see the linked `vim.filetype` issue).\n\nCan't we at least return a subset? That's less bad than the current situation, where (AFAIU) we have no idea what `vim.filetype.add()` filetypes were registered?\n\nIs there currently any way for users to inspect the structures maintained by `vim.filetype.add()` ?",
